cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO 

The paper deals with learning object-annotation alignments from a dataset with annotations affected by geometric noise, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a method based on deep neural networks, which involves training the network to correct the annotations given only noisy annotations as input. This involves the use of a consistency loss, which is a common technique in machine learning. Therefore, the paper is also likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper also involves the use of self-supervised learning, which is a technique used in unsupervised learning. Therefore, the paper is also likely to belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper also involves the use of spatial memory maps, which are commonly used in robotics and control systems. Therefore, the paper is also likely to belong to the cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.RO (Robotics) categories.
